data.meta_description: GreekStudy is an iOS and Android app for recording academic and Greek study hours

Sign up for a free trial

My Greek Study is now GreekStudy! We will be transitioning all branding and materials to the new brand name as the year progresses.

About

GreekStudy is an application for mobile devices and the web to monitor your member's study hours!

It keeps track of how long they are actually in your designated study locations. You can set each member's minimum study hours, fines for missing hours, and at the end of each week, you and your members receive reports automatically.

Call 256-710-6966

Monday - Saturday 9am-9pm CST

Automatic Reports No longer have to retrieve paper logs or manage an Excel sheet. GreekStudy does it all for you!

Improve GPA Prevents members from cheating the system. Improve your organization and members' GPA

Unlimited Study Locations Your members can study at as many study locations as you would like

Unlimited Members Each organization may have as many user members as necessary. No limits!

Members' Hours Set each member's hours individually. These can be changed at any time for penalty or bonus

Time Controlled Study Locations Set the times you would like the study location to be enabled

Council Control Greek councils that sign up for GreekStudy can view and access all of the chapters study information

Member Specific Locations Want only a certain member or group of members to study at a location? GreekStudy allows you to assign locations to members of your choosing

Early College Study Programs GreekStudy is great for early college programs! Track and prepare students for their upcoming college career

How does it work?

GreekStudy uses GPS technology in order to track members location. Once the member enters the building, the app recognizes they are inside and allows them to start the timer for studying. Your organization may have as many study locations, both on and off campus, as needed.

Administrators receive an automatic report every week detailing who made study hours and who did not. This report can easily be forwarded to your treasurer for fining. Users also receive a weekly automated email displaying their hours, if they met the required hours, and what their fine is if they did not. Chapter advsiors can also be added! They receive weekly reports and can view how their chapter is doing on the website.

Don't worry about security or privacy when it comes to GreekStudy. The application does not save location data in any way. It only checks to see if a user's phone is in the radius of a study location and then discards the information.

Reviews from customers

Catherine ForemanDelta Phi Epsilon, Georgia Southern University GreekStudy has proven to be a wonderful tool in my sorority. It holds my sisters accountable and motivates them with their study hours. The thing my chapter enjoys most is being able to physically see how much you study and watching their hours add up! The team at GreekStudy is also fantastic when it comes to handling any issues that we might have. They are extremely timely in answering your support requests! I think the quickest I've had someone get back to me was 20 minutes! I recommend this to anyone who is looking for an easy way to mainstream their process of logging study hours. You won't be disappointed.

Amanda IvyAlpha Chi Omega, University of Alabama "GreekStudy has made study hall so much more efficient for our chapter. It allows girls to study in more locations than they were able to before, and its easier for me to keep up with hours electronically. GreekStudy is an awesome app that I would recommend to any greek organization!"

Katie DuranceauUniversity of Central Florida "As the newest Greek organization on campus and one without a house, it is hard to be able to hold and record study hours for the 160+ girls in our organization. GreekStudy allows us to be able to let the girls not only study on their own time, but also make sure their time is getting accurately recorded. GreekStudy has been extremely beneficial in helping to improve and maintain our organizationÃ¢â¬â¢s scholastics as a whole."

Noah MuszallArmstrong State University "As scholarship chair for the Georgia Rho Colony of Sigma Alpha Epsilon, I am responsible for keeping up with everyone's study habits and school work. GreekStudy has cut down on brothers missing study hours due to the fine that is handed out if the brothers do not complete their mandatory hours each week. Not only does this website make my job easier, it helps improve the grades of all of the brothers of Georgia Rho."
